Sky Blade

Calling on the power of Gaea, the druid forges
a piece of the sky into a scythelike weapon.
This weapon is weightless and in addition, can
be commanded at the time of its creation to deal
different types of damage.  Depending on the
Druid's mastery level and alignment, these
may include:

magic - pure magical damage
fire - flame damage (good only)
holy - holy damage through Gaea's light side (good only)
unholy - unholy damage through Gaea's dark side (evil only)
cold - cold damage (evil only)
void - damage from the night
lightning - damage from the storm
rain - damage from immersion

Command: skyblade <type> (defaults to magic)
Base Cost: 60 SP
Base Recovery: medium-long
Base Effect: create items (weapon)
Base Duration: long
Guild Level: 9
